latestPosts.caption:
al fresco happy hour essentials ✨ ~ #ad i adore a good deck happy hr. situation during the summer months + i’ve created a bit of a hosting recipe over the years that lends itself to festive but casual vibes:

+ a salty, light, crunchy snack - our absolute favorite is @gardenveggiesnacks - we love these better for you, easily shareable snacks! 👏🏻 they’re certified gluten-free and are fun, light, colorful, and simply irresistible! while we think all of their flavors are delicious, we particularly love the classic Sea Salt Garden Veggie Straws® and the Mac n’ Cheese Garden Veggie™ Puffs. ✨ to find where you can purchase Garden Veggie Snacks, click the link in my profile!

+ plates/napkins/silverware - i typically don’t do paper - i like to use our actual plates & cloth napkins - bc, well, what else are we saving it for? 🍽️ 

+ a pitcher of water/drinks - trust me, water always goes so quickly, especially when you have it sitting out for your guests! it’s all about easy access here. 💦 

+ music - an absolute MUST imo - no deck happy hr. is complete without a lil’ tunes to set the vibe. 🎶 

+ for fun/extras/you totally don’t have to add these but it’s fun if you do: a tablecloth (i’m a huge fan of gingham & stripes for added flair) + you could even add some fresh flowers - no need to run to the store- just cut them from your yard! 🌸

#hostingtips #entertainingathome #happyhoursnacks #summersnacks
